   <text facs="facs:RE-WhatMenWant1">
      <body>
         <opener>
            <dateline>
               <date>Feb. 19th, 1930</date>
            </dateline>
            <byline><name ref="pers:CGS1">C. Gardner Sullivan</name>
               <name ref="pers:WE1">Winnifred Reeve</name></byline>
         </opener>

         <div type="content">

            <p>RE: WHAT MEN WANT</p>

            <p>May I ask that the umbrella gag, which is original with me, be left out of the new
               version of <q>WHAT MEN WANT</q>? I would like very much to use this incident in some
               other story that I might write for Universal.</p>

            <p>I read the new version and it follows in the main my original adaptation - - values,
               characterizations and even incidents but is treated differently, with the added
               incident of Lee being the mistress of some man which you personally suggested. You
               may recall I wrote an outline based on your idea.</p>

            <p>Personally, I think the first version is the best, but of course I’m prejudiced. I
               maintain however that there is more drama to it and the characters are more real and
               there is a <foreign xml:lang="fr">raison d’etre</foreign> for their actions. This is
               not meant in any way as criticism of the new version, for I hope my mind is
               sufficiently elastic to allow for the opinions of others.</p>

            <p>Although many of my ideas are embodied in the new version I would much prefer not to
               have my name on this.</p>


         </div>
      </body>
